parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of front lap belts and malfunctioning shoulder belts can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: No front lap belts
shoulder belts do not lock properly during sudden stops
occupants may not be properly restrained in the event of an accident.

sudden acceleration

open throttle position at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.

inability to stop the vehicle

vehicle takes longer than usual to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handles can cause inconvenience, difficulty, or impossibility in entering or exiting the vehicle, which can lead to safety issues, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door handles break off
the trigger breaks in the door handle
the door handles are unable to open the door
the door handles are loose or fragile.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause coolant to leak into the passenger compartment, creating a hazardous environment for occupants due to the potential for scalding and reduced visibility from fogged windows.
symptoms: Smoke or steam emanates from the vents
windows fog up or steam up
coolant leaks into the passenger compartment
sweet or burning smell inside the vehicle.
